modules.description: Encodes and decodes data using Recursive Length Prefix (RLP) serialization, handling lists and byte sequences. It processes nested structures, including arbitrary-depth lists and mixed-type elements. Used for serializing structured data in blockchain protocols and peer-to-peer networks.

Encodes integers and big integers into RLP data elements, decodes byte strings into RLP trees, and converts RLP structures to JSON-like strings or byte sequences. Operates on integer values, big integers, and RLP trees represented as a custom type. Used for serializing structured data in blockchain protocols, ensuring canonical encoding and decoding of nested structures.
